metadata.title: Beechcraft Bonanza
aws::graph::propositions: Beechcraft Bonanza Model Variants
14 Model 35s were modified to a special standard.
Each modified Model 35 had a suffix "R1" through "R14" appended to their original serial numbers.
D35 was a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
D35 was introduced in 1953.
D35 was a C35 with increased takeoff weight.
D35 had minor changes from the C35.
D35 was approved for the Lycoming GO-435-D1 engine.
298 D35 aircraft were built.
E35 was a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
E35 was introduced in 1954.
E35 was powered by E-185-11 engine.
E35 was alternatively powered by 225 hp (168 kW) Continental E-225-8 engine.
301 E35 aircraft were built.
F35 was a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
F35 was introduced in 1955.
F35 was powered by E-185-11 engine.
F35 was alternatively powered by E-225-8 engine.
F35 had an extra rear window on each side.
F35 had strengthened wing leading edges.
F35 had strengthened tail spar caps.
392 F35 aircraft were built.
G35 was a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
G35 was introduced in 1956.
G35 was powered by Continental E-225-8 engine.
G35 had a thicker windshield.
476 G35 aircraft were built.
H35 was a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
H35 was introduced in 1957.
H35 was powered by a 240 hp (180 kW) Continental O-470-G engine.
H35 had a modified structure.
464 H35 aircraft were built.

text:
14 Model 35s were modified to this standard, with each having the suffix "R1" through "R14" appended to their original serial numbers.
D35
(1953) C35 with increased takeoff weight and minor changes, approved for the Lycoming GO-435-D1 engine. 298 built.
E35
(1954) Powered by E-185-11 or 225 hp (168 kW) Continental E-225-8 engine, 301 built.
F35
(1955) Powered by E-185-11 or E-225-8 engine. Extra rear window each side, strengthened wing leading edges and tail spar caps. 392 built.
G35
(1956) Powered by Continental E-225-8 engine, thicker windshield. 476 built.
H35

(1957) Powered by a 240 hp (180 kW) Continental O-470-G engine, and with modified structure. 464 built.
